<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
     <title> Production of Automobiles</title> 
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        /* Custom CSS for styling the page */
        body {
            
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        .main-section {
            margin: 50px 0;
        }

        .production-title {
            font-size: 3em;
            /* color: white; */
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            animation: fadeInDown 1s ease-in-out;
        }

        .production-text {
            font-size: 1.2em;
            color: #495057;
            text-align: justify;
            line-height: 1.6;
            animation: fadeIn 1.5s ease-in-out;
        }

        .section-title {
            color: #007bff;
            margin-top: 40px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .section-text {
            text-align: justify;
        }

        /* Keyframe animations */
        @keyframes fadeIn {
            0% {
                opacity: 0;
            }

            100% {
                opacity: 1;
            }
        }

        @keyframes fadeInDown {
            0% {
                opacity: 0;
                transform: translateY(-20px);
            }

            100% {
                opacity: 1;
                transform: translateY(0);
            }
        }

        @keyframes slideIn {
            0% {
                opacity: 0;
                transform: translateX(-30px);
            }

            100% {
                opacity: 1;
                transform: translateX(0);
            }
        }

        .d-flex {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: flex-end;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }

        .section-text {
            margin-left: 30px;
            max-width: 400px;
            font-size: 22px;
            font-family: ui-monospace;
        }

        .card {
            width: 300px;
        }

        /* Animation for images */
        .animated-image {
            animation: slideIn 1s ease forwards;
        }
        .card-text{
            color: black;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    
    <%- include('partials/navbar1') %>

    <!-- Main Container -->
    <div class="container main-section">
        <h1 class="production-title">Production in Automobiles</h1>

        <h3 class="section-title">1. Design and Development</h3>

        <div class="d-flex align-items-start">
            <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <img id="image1" src="/static/production1.jpg" class="card-img-top animated-image" alt="">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="card-text">Cad Design</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="section-text">
                The journey begins with conceptual designs and prototypes. Automakers use advanced tools like CAD
                (Computer-Aided Design) to create digital models of the vehicle. Prototypes are then developed and
                tested for aerodynamics, safety, and performance before moving forward.
            </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="section-title">2. Sourcing Material</h3>

        <div class="d-flex align-items-start engine-production-container">
            <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <img id="image2" src="/static/production2.webp" class="card-img-top animated-image" alt="">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="card-text">Power Battery</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="section-text">
                After the design is finalized, raw materials such as steel, aluminum, battery, plastic, and rubber are sourced.
                Automakers work with suppliers worldwide to ensure they have the necessary components, like engines,
                transmissions, electronics, and software. 
            </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="section-title">3. Manufacturing and Assembly</h3>

        <div class="d-flex align-items-start manufacturing-container">
            <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <img id="image3" src="/static/production3.jpg" class="card-img-top animated-image" alt="">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="card-text">Robotics Arm</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="section-text">
                The actual production begins with stamping and molding body panels and assembling parts like the engine
                and drivetrain. Advanced robotics handle precision tasks like welding, while human workers ensure
                quality and consistency in more complex assembly tasks.
            </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="section-title">4. Engine and Powertrain Production</h3>

        <div class="d-flex align-items-start engine-production-container">
            <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <img id="image4" src="/static/production4.jpg" class="card-img-top animated-image" alt="">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="card-text">Engine </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="section-text">
                Engines are assembled separately, combining precision engineering with complex components like
                cylinders, pistons, and crankshafts. The powertrain, responsible for transmitting power from the engine
                to the wheels, is built in this stage.
            </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="section-title">5. Testing and Quality Assurance</h3>

        <div class="d-flex align-items-start testing-container">
            <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <img id="image5" src="/static/production5.jpg" class="card-img-top animated-image" alt="">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="card-text">Quality Checking</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="section-text">
                After assembly, cars undergo rigorous testing for safety, performance, and emissions standards. This
                ensures that each vehicle meets high standards for quality before itâ€™s released for sale.
            </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="section-title">6. Final Assembly</h3>

        <div class="d-flex align-items-start final-assembly-container">
            <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <img id="image6" src="/static/production6.jpg" class="card-img-top animated-image" alt="">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="card-text">Ready To Drive</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="section-text">
                Once the testing phase is complete, the vehicle's final components are added, and it's prepared for
                shipment. Automakers emphasize safety, comfort, and performance, ensuring each car is ready to provide
                an excellent driving experience.
            </p>
        </div>








        <%- include('partials/footer1') %>

        <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    </div>

</body>

</html>
